approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `amount` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params.tokensToBurn: The number of tokens to burn

params.comment: A comment associated with the buy order
params.expectedMarketType: The expected market type (0 = BONDING_CURVE, 1 = UNISWAP_POOL)
params.minOrderSize: The minimum tokens to prevent slippage
params.recipient: The address to receive the purchased tokens
params.refundRecipient: The address to receive any excess ETH
params.sqrtPriceLimitX96: The price limit for Uniswap V3 pool swaps, ignored if market is bonding curve.

decimals().details: Returns the number of decimals used to get its user representation. For example, if `decimals` equals `2`, a balance of `505` tokens should be displayed to a user as `5.05` (`505 / 10 ** 2`). Tokens usually opt for a value of 18, imitating the relationship between Ether and Wei. This is the default value returned by this function, unless it's overridden. NOTE: This information is only used for _display_ purposes: it in no way affects any of the arithmetic of the contract, including {IERC20-balanceOf} and {IERC20-transfer}.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically decreases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address. - `spender` must have allowance for the caller of at least `subtractedValue`.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: Atomically increases the allowance granted to `spender` by the caller. This is an alternative to {approve} that can be used as a mitigation for problems described in {IERC20-approve}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

params._bondingCurve: The address of the bonding curve module

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: For receiving the Uniswap V3 LP NFT on market graduation.

params.comment: A comment associated with the sell order
params.expectedMarketType: The expected market type (0 = BONDING_CURVE, 1 = UNISWAP_POOL)
params.minPayoutSize: The minimum ETH payout to prevent slippage
params.recipient: The address to receive the ETH payout
params.sqrtPriceLimitX96: The price limit for Uniswap V3 pool swaps, ignored if market is bonding curve
params.tokensToSell: The number of tokens to sell

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `amount`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Emits an {Approval} event indicating the updated allowance. This is not required by the EIP. See the note at the beginning of {ERC20}. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `amount`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `amount`.

uniswapV3SwapCallback(int256,int256,byte.details: No-op to allow a swap on the pool to set the correct initial price, if needed

burn(uint256).notice: Burns tokens after the market has graduated to Uniswap V3

buy(address,address,string,uint8,uint256.notice: Purchases tokens using ETH, either from the bonding curve or Uniswap V3 pool

convictionNFT().notice: Returns the address of the Conviction NFT contract

currentExchangeRate().notice: The current exchange rate of the token if the market has not graduated.         This will revert if the market has graduated to the Uniswap V3 pool.

getCurrentPrice().notice: Returns the current price from Uniswap pool or 0 if in bonding curve

getEthBuyQuote(uint256).notice: The number of tokens that can be bought from a given amount of ETH.         This will revert if the market has graduated to the Uniswap V3 pool.

getEthSellQuote(uint256).notice: The number of tokens for selling a given amount of ETH.         This will revert if the market has graduated to the Uniswap V3 pool.

getTokenBuyQuote(uint256).notice: The amount of ETH needed to buy a given number of tokens.         This will revert if the market has graduated to the Uniswap V3 pool.

getTokenSellQuote(uint256).notice: The amount of ETH that can be received for selling a given number of tokens.         This will revert if the market has graduated to the Uniswap V3 pool.

sell(uint256,address,string,uint8,uint25.notice: Sells tokens for ETH, either to the bonding curve or Uniswap V3 pool

state().notice: Returns current market type and address

tokenURI().notice: Returns the URI of the token
